  "texts": [
    "In this paper, we do not attempt to answer what states are.",
    "Instead, we delegate this task to the LLM, allowing it to infer states.",
    "This approach has proven effective.Fuzzing based on Large Language Models: Following the remarkable success of pre-trained large language models (LLMs) in various natural language processing tasks, researchers have been exploring their potential in diverse domains, including in fuzzing.",
    "For instance, CODAMOSA [28] was the first to apply LLMs to fuzzing (i.e., the automatic generation of test cases for Python modules).",
    "Later, TITAN-FUZZ [17] and FUZZGPT [18] used an LLM to automatically generate test cases for Deep Learning software libraries, specifically."
  ],
